releases.name: poi v7.3.0
releases.body:
# Feature
- FCD (Frequently Changing Data) Module
  - frequent updated data are included in this module, including map, ship tagging and last dance HP
  - every release of poi will contain a copy of FCD data, and poi will download the updates upon initialization
  - FCD data can be updated without upgrading main poi version
  - FCD version can be check on About panel, where manually update is also possible
- Airbase information update for multiple areas supported
- Alphabetic map cell name supported 
- Jet plane related functionalities
- Flash display mode settings
- Fighter power without proficiency and improvement bonus is added
- Add thanks-to to about page

# Bugfix
- Retreated ship display, and Fighter Power formula takes retreats into account
- Mini map display for map cells uncovered in map data
- Network retry settings
- Occasionally `remote` exceptions (e.g. game audio switch) introduced by `Electron`
- Cursor jumping issue on Windows with HiDPI display setting

releases.name: poi v5.2.0
releases.body:
# 5.2.0

> Update patch is available for 5.1.0 and later versions.

## Features
- Added "Menu" to Windows and Linux.
  - Menu is visible by pressing Alt. It is also available by right clicking the tray icon on Windows.
  - Options including "Window resizable" and "Window always on top" are moved to the menu.
- Moving your mouse over equipment icons on the main panel will now prompt equipment stats.
- Now support changes brought in by 16Winter event.

## Fixes
- Improved the auto-adjustment of Flash size.
- Improved the rendering efficiency of the main panel.
- More icons in the main panel support HD icons.
- Fixed a problem that prevents "Muted" to be applied on the start up of poi.
- Fixed a problem that causes a number of tray icons to appear in Windows.
- Fixed a problem where poi will not properly start when anti-virus softwares prevent poi from creating shortcut.
- Notification audio will only set off once if multiple notifications set off during a short time.

releases.name: poi v5.1.0
releases.body:
## Features
- Added "PAC file" to proxy settings. (Experimental feature)
- Added support for individual settings of plugins.
  - (However, the only supporting plugin "Prophet" has yet to really apply that setting. So please look forward to future versions.)
- Added installation progress notification when installing plugin by plugin-name.
- Added shortcut `Cmd+,`  (comma) to switch to Settings panel under OS X.
- Added transition animation when switching between panels.
- Add option for "poi port" under Network Settings panel.
  - The default behaviour is to use a random port on every start up.
  - You can change and set a fixed port as poi used to do. In this case, an alert will pop up if that port has been used on start up.

## Fixes
- Fixed an issue that could prevent a plugin from being properly installed by name.
- The limit on resolution of Flash is now stricter and will take consideration of zoomming.
- poi will no longer shrink to a low resolution when opening another low-resolution programming.
- The settings panel will be able to scroll from the very beginning of the start up.
- The notification sound effect of Windows will no longer be also triggered upon notification.
- Changed the default theme therefore fixing an issue that may cause poi to be unresponsive at a fresh start.
- The interface of modernization notification has been polished.
- Switching between single tab and double tab now no longer requires a restart, but some plugins might need the flash to refresh in order to properly work.
- Fixed an issue that causes the window to be out of the visible screen in some cases.

## Plugins
- New plugin: **Where's My Fuel Gone**
  - Records the resource consumption during sortie. Filter, analyse.
- New plugin: **Kcwiki data collection**
  - Automatically collect data and reports to Kcwiki, `http://zh.kcwiki.moe/`, including ship stats, map resources, among others. Please support the construction of our wiki if possible :)
- Logbook
  - Removed the "Senka" panel (this feature has been provided by another plugin "SenkaCalc"), therefore solving an issue that causes this plugin to crash under some cases.
- Prophet
  - Data will now be refreshed when changing composition and docking.

### Feature
- Added a new npm mirror (plugin source), taobao, which is now default to `zh-**` systems.

### Bugfix
- Fixed the problem where plugin tarballs may fail to install in some cases.
  - Plugins are now packaged into `.tgz` tarballs (instead of `.tar.gz`) before packaged into a `.7z` archive.

- Now supports the audio for "Heavily damaged notification".

releases.name: poi v5.0.0-beta.0
releases.body:
### General

#### Introducing the brand new "Plugin manager"

Plugins are now separate parts from the main poi. They can now be downloaded, enabled/disabled, upgraded independently. This will especially benefit those information-based plugins that needs updating with every update of the game, such as "Quest Information", so that they don't have to wait for the next release of poi just to add a few lines. Also, plugins can now be updated at a more regular basis.
- Management of the plugins
  - Plugins are no longer included in the release archive of main poi. Instead, you will download them manually inside the settings panel after you launched the new poi. Don't worry, that's just a click on the button.
  - Plugins are no longer stored in the `plugins` folder inside the root of main poi. Instead, they are moved into somewhere inside your user folder of the operating system. Plugins are removed if you delete the main poi.
- Downloading plugins
  - You can choose from the several mirrors provided in the advanced plugin settings. An accessible mirror also enables you to receive plugin update notifications.
  - For those users to whom none of the mirrors is accessible, they can install a plugin from its offline plugin tarball.
  - An offline plugin tarball is simply a `tar.gz` archived file that wraps a plugin.
  - A collection the offline tarball of the official plugins (see below) with the most recent version will be provided with every release of main poi.
- Official plugins and third-party plugins
  - A list of "official plugins", which are those developed and maintained by the poi team, is included along with main poi. 
  - Official plugins will appear in the plugin list with a "not installed" status even if you haven't installed them.
  - We also encourages the development of third-party plugins.
  - Third-party plugins should be published on [npmjs.com](npmjs.com) with prefix `poi-plugin-` so that it can be easily searched and recognized. 
  - Third-party plugins can be installed by simply providing the plugin name. They can also be installed, of course, with offline tarballs.
  - You can search for plugins from the plugin settings.
- We will summarize the update of official plugins between every major updates in the release changelog.

### Features
- A new set of HD icons, in replacement of the original icons, is available under the display settings. This is expected to enhance the display on HD screens.
  - The new icons adopted flat design rather than the original quasi-physical style to stay consistent with the other part of poi, which makes it look a little unfamiliar at first sight. 
  - Nevertheless, it's still in progress and we are looking forward to your feedback.
- Introducing "Tips". Shown in the status bar at start-up and every half hour hereafter, it includes unnoticed features, precautions, and other trivia about poi. 
  - You can disable it in the settings.
- "Modernization-delta".
  - The result of a modernization (merging) will be displayed in the status bar. The amount of improvement of each status will be listed.
  - As you may have known or not known, each status that is under modernization ends up either "adding all" or "adding around half" for the basic four properties, and "round up" or "round down" for Luck. The previous case will be displayed as "++" and the latter case "+".
- The control bar can now be collapsed. Less common buttons are hidden inside by default.
- The map-reminder will now display the difficulty of an event map.
- More options to notification: you can now control the line of fatigue recovery, and the period of time that you want to be noticed in advance before an expedition returns.
- More options to sortie check: you can now set the number of vacancies of both ship and equipment.
- Added customization of boss key.
  - For Mac users: there is a global boss key `Cmd+H` for every application.
- Added customization of cache directory.
- Added percentage specification when setting the flash resolution.
- Added option "Prevent DMM Network Change Popup" because it sometimes annoys people.
- Minor UI fixes.
- The scripts are now precompiled before release; in another word, we expect it shortens the start-up time.
- The poi app is now archived as a `asar` package. The influences are:
  - Almost no more path-too-long errors.
  - The extraction of the release archive of poi will be much faster.
  - The update patch will be `app.asar` from now on instead of `app.7z`.

### Plugin updates
- Prophet
  - Notices you when any item drops from sortie, including but not limited to Present Boxes and Decoration Materials this time.
- Exp Calc
  - Level limit rose to 155.
  - Shows at the poi status bar the experiences you'll get from an exercise opponent, and the bonuses you get from Training Cruisers.
  - When specifying a ship that has passed its own remodel level, the target level will display the level of the next remodel if available.
- Quest Information
  - Added English and Japanese translation for the requirement and reward of all quests.
  - Added latest quests.
  - Fixed some prerequisite information.
- Composition Record (originally named Hensei Nikki)
  - Rearranged display.
  - You can now preview the composition of your current fleets in "import" without actually adding them.
- Logbook
  - Minor UI fixes. Minor compatibility enhancement. Minor effects added.
- Equipment Improvement
  - A tickbox is added in front of each row to highlight your interested equipment!
- Ship Girls Info
  - New filter added: Modernization completed
- Equipment Info
  - Planes are now listed with their aircraft proficiency.
  - The number equipped is displayed if multiple pieces of equipment are on the same ship.
  - UI fixes.

#### New plugin: Translator

Translate ship names, equipment names, item names (and probably more) into English, by installing this plugin (and setting language to English)!

#### New plugin: Senka Calc

Head for the monthly ranking award? Track your admiral rank and the overall rankings in your server, here!

#### New plugin: Secretary

Change the notification sound from "poi" to your waifu by setting her your secretary!

#### (Reintroduce) Plugin: Almanac

Failed LSC again? Taiha on the first point of sortie? Probably because you didn't follow this almanac! Find your fortune here.
- We are not responsible for any consequences, either good or bad, from taking this seriously, though.
- This plugin has long existed but we didn't include it before.

releases.name: poi v4.2.0/v4.2.1
releases.body:
**General**
- Updated data for 15Fall Event.

**Features**
- Removed built-in shadowsocks module for being outdated.
- Changed the cache directory in Windows.
- [Prophet] Added map information of 15Fall Event for compass prediction.
- [Battle detail] Usage of damage control personnels is now indicated by an icon.
- [Expedition] Added condition for the two expeditions of 15Fall event.

**Bugfix**
- [Expedition] Expedition 15 now allows armored carriers.
- [Quests] Fixed a mistake in the quest condition from the Mitsumoto series.
- [Hensei Nikki] Fixed crashing when deleting a fleet record that is empty.
- [Report] This plugin now correctly stops reporting data after being disabled in the settings.
- [Ship info] Now correctly remembers the last window position.

# v4.2.1

**Bugfix**
- Fixed the bug that caused cache merging with user cache in Windows in v4.2.0.

releases.name: poi v4.1.0
releases.body:
**Feature**
- The ship info panel now supports the new fleet expansion and equipment exchange feature.
- The directory to screenshots can now be customized in settings.
- A new theme _darklykai_.
- [Quest] Updated to the latest quests.
- [Battle detail] New features.
  - The HP lost in the current round now displays in shadow.
  - The HP recovered from damage control personnels is now correctly calculated.
  - Added "Battle info" panel. Click that title to expand.
- [Hensei Nikki] Now supports aircraft proficiency in the fleet code from Who Calls the Fleet.
- [Prophet] Now correct the MVP fleet according to the battle result received.
- [Fleet info] New features.
  - The table headers are now clickable to sort the corresponding column.
  - New filter: whether a ship can remodel.

**Bugfix**
- The icons of regenerating resources now normally glow.
- The dropdown menu of plugin selection are now scrollable when too long.
- Vertical layout now correctly adjusts the window in non-standard zooming and width settings.
- Proxy settings are reworded to avoid confusion.
- [Akashic records] Fixed some no-responding problems.
- [Quest] Fixed prerequisites of some tasks according to jp-wiki.
- [Hensei Nikki] Now correctly handles LOS.
